'''''Rust Bucket''''' was the [[Starship/Legends|starship]] belonging to [[Tann]], the brother of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] soldier [[Surna]]. It named after an old family joke and was a small [[Corellian Engineering Corporation/Legends|Corellian Engineering Corporation]] stock light freighter, older than the [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]]. Tann purchased the freighter using credits borrowed from [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]]. Tann was unable to earn enough credits to maintain his repayments to Jabba after he was grounded during the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] blockade of the planet [[Toprawa/Legends|Toprawa]]. The ship was subsequently impounded by agents working for Jabba.<ref name="BH">''[[The Bounty Hunter]]''</ref>

In a high-stakes game of [[seven card comet]], rebel soldier and fledgling [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Havet Storm]] won enough credits to free ''Rust Bucket''. Surna, Tann and a few other rebels then used the ship to break through the Imperial blockade and escape the planet. Once away from Toprawa, the band of rebels used the freighter to seek out and rejoin the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]].<ref name="BH" />

